- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 6 positive samples linked to the Jigawa outbreak in 2021.

Mozambique
- 2 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported; 1 each in the provinces of Nampula and Cabo Delgado. These cases have an onset in 2021.

Niger
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains at 15.

Nigeria
- 16 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported; 1 each in Anambra and Oyo, 2 each in Kaduna and Zamfara, 7 in Kebbi and 3 in Sokoto bringing the number of 2021 cases to 413.
- 18 positive environmental samples were reported; 1 each in Adamawa, Kaduna, Kogi and Osun, 2 each in Borno and Katsina, 3 each in Gombe and Sokoto and 4 in Kano.

Senegal
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 17 cases reported in 2021.

Sierra Leone
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 5 cases in 2021.

