[This week's report has several noteworthy events. One noteworthy report has 2 cVDPV2 associated AFP cases in Mozambique. The last cVDPV2 associated AFP case reported in Mozambique had onset of illness in 2018, and the last WPV associated case reported from Mozambique was in 1993 (https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/mm5222a3.htm#tab1). Another noteworty occurrence is the report of additional environment samples that isolated cVDPV2 in Djibouti (with the 1st isolates noted in a weekly report on 2 Feb 2022 - see Poliomyelitis update (03): WPV1 (AFP Afghanistan), cVDPV2 (AFP; ES Djibouti) 20220212.8701429). These isolates were from samples obtained on 10 Dec 2021 (https://polioeradication.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/weekly-polio-analyses-cVDPV-20220215.pdf). And last, although not least, the 1st cVDPV2 associated AFP case with onset of illness in 2022 was reported in Somalia. Transmission with resultant AFP cases associated with cVDPV2 infection continues to occur in Nigeria. It is discouraging that every week or 2 there are new countries identifying and reporting cVDPVs, consistent with lower vaccine coverages leaving increasingly bigger pockets of susceptibles.

A map showing the location of each confirmed case of polio worldwide in the past 12 months can be found at https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. One can see cases of cVDPV in a band across Africa and in Tajikistan, Afghanistan and Pakistan, cVDPV1 in Madagascar and Yemen, and WPV1 in Afghanistan and Pakistan. - Mod.MPP]

